11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 11 O.S. 2021, Section 49-101, as
13 amended by Section 3, Chapter 232, O.S.L. 2022 (11 O.S. Supp. 2025,
14 Section 49-101), is amended to read as follows:
15 Section 49-101. A. All retired volunteer firefighters who
16 qualify for retirement shall be entitled to a monthly pension. The
17 monthly pension of a volunteer firefighter who retires prior to the
18 effective date of this act shall be in the amount retired volunteer
19 firefighters are receiving at the time the volunteer firefighter
20 begins to receive a pension for each year of credited service not to
21 exceed thirty (30) years. Volunteer firefighters who retire on and
22 after the effective date of this act shall receive a monthly pension
23 in the amount of Ten Dollars ($10.00) for each year of credited
24 service not to exceed thirty (30) years. In determining the number
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB432 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

RBS No. 354
1 of y ears of credited service, a fractional year of six (6) months or
2 more shall be counted as one (1) full year and a fractional year of
3 less than six (6) months shall not be counted in such determination.
4 Retired volunteer firefighters of a municipality shall receive a
5 pension of not less than that which retired volunteer firefighters
6 of such municipality were receiving on June 30, 1985.
7 B. A volunteer firefighter who terminates service after
8 completing ten (10) years of credited service, but less than twenty
9 (20) years of credited service, shall be entitled to receive a
10 vested benefit commencing on the date the firefighter reaches fifty
11 (50) years of age or the date the firefighter would have had twenty
12 (20) years of credited service had the firefighter’s service
13 continued uninterrupted, whichever is later. The monthly amount of
14 such retirement benefit shall be the amount being paid to volunteer
15 firefighters at the time the member vests multiplied by the number
16 of years of credited service. Credited service must be established
17 at the time of the volunteer firefighter’s termination. If a
18 volunteer firefighter who terminated employment and elected, or was
19 eligible to elect, a vested benefit dies prior to being eligible to
20 receive benefits, the volunteer firefighter’s beneficiary, as
21 defined in paragraph 16 of Section 49-100.1 of this title, shall be
22 entitled to the volunteer firefighter’s normal monthly retirement
23 benefit on the date the deceased volunteer firefighter would have
24 been eligible to receive the benefit.
