RBS No. 354
1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 11 O.S. 2021, Section 49-101.2, as
2 amended by Section 4, Chapter 232, O.S.L. 2022 (11 O.S. Supp. 2025,
3 Section 49-101.2), is amended to read as follows:
4 Section 49-101.2. Any member serving as an active volunteer
5 firefighter who receives annual compensation from the fire
6 department the firefighter is enrolled in as a member of the
7 Oklahoma Firefighters Pension and Retirement System for services
8 related to firefighting, other than reimbursement of expenses in
9 excess of five and one-half (5 1/2) times the annual pension benefit
10 paid by the System to a retired volunteer firefighter with twenty
11 (20) years credited service Nine Thousand Nine Hundred Thirty-nine
12 Dollars and sixty-nine cents ($9,939.69), shall be considered a paid
13 firefighter and must meet the physical and agility requirements
14 pursuant to Section 49-116 of this title to continue as an active
15 member of the System. Credited service earned as a paid firefighter
16 pursuant to this section shall not be considered actual experience
17 as a paid firefighter for purposes of meeting the qualifications of
18 a paid fire chief as provided in Section 29-102 of this title. No
19 fire department of a participating municipality shall employ a
20 volunteer firefighter from another fire department to perform
21 services relating to firefighting for any compensation of any kind.
22 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON RETIREMENT AND GOVERNMENT
